//! Object-centric event schema (OCEL): activity codes and the object types each activity
//! links to, mirrored from the pattern ontology. See [`crate::evidence::ocel`].
//!
//! # OCEL Schema Connection
//!
//! The Object-Centric Event Log (OCEL) model tracks *which object types* each event
//! activity involves. This module mirrors that schema as flat Rust data so that
//! admission-contract checks and replay verification can query schema membership
//! without deserializing the full ontology at runtime.
//!
//! Each [`OcelSchemaEdge`] represents one `(activity, object-type)` edge from the
//! SPARQL query `ggen/queries/ocel_schema.rq` over `ggen/schema/patterns.ttl`.
//! The edges are ordered by `(pattern_id, object_type)` for deterministic iteration.
//!
//! To check whether a given `(event_code, object_code)` pair is schema-valid:
//!
//! ```ignore
//! use wasm4games::evidence::ocel_schema::OCEL_SCHEMA;
//! let valid = OCEL_SCHEMA.iter().any(|e| e.activity == event_code && e.object_type == obj_code);
//! ```

/// One (activity, object-type) edge of the OCEL schema.
///
/// Derived from the `w4g:touchesObject` predicate in `ggen/schema/patterns.ttl`.
/// Each edge asserts that the pattern with `pattern_id` emits events of type
